"{\"uid\": \"thefederalist.com-2024-03-29-scientists-rebut-the-olympic-committees-misguided-policies-on-testosterone-levels\", \"noun_phrases\": [{\"sentence\": \"A new published report from international researchers marshals every line of evidence in defense of fairness in women's sports.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 127, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"A new published report\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 22}, {\"ngram\": \"international researchers marshals\", \"from\": 28, \"to\": 62}, {\"ngram\": \"every line\", \"from\": 63, \"to\": 73}, {\"ngram\": \"evidence\", \"from\": 77, \"to\": 85}, {\"ngram\": \"defense\", \"from\": 89, \"to\": 96}, {\"ngram\": \"fairness\", \"from\": 100, \"to\": 108}, {\"ngram\": \"women's sports\", \"from\": 112, \"to\": 126}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The International Olympic Committee (IOC) developed its 2021 framework on sex and \\\"gender\\\" around the concepts of fairness, inclusion, and non-discrimination.\", \"from\": 129, \"to\": 287, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 133, \"end\": 170, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"International Olympic Committee (IOC)\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\"}, {\"begin\": 133, \"end\": 170, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"International Olympic Committee (IOC)\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"its 2021 framework\", \"from\": 181, \"to\": 199}, {\"ngram\": \"sex\", \"from\": 203, \"to\": 206}, {\"ngram\": \"\\\"gender\", \"from\": 211, \"to\": 218}, {\"ngram\": \"the concepts\", \"from\": 227, \"to\": 239}, {\"ngram\": \"fairness\", \"from\": 243, \"to\": 251}, {\"ngram\": \"inclusion\", \"from\": 253, \"to\": 262}, {\"ngram\": \"discrimination\", \"from\": 272, \"to\": 286}]}, {\"sentence\": \"This framework leaves it toeach sport's governing body\\\"to determine how an athlete may be at a disproportionate advantage against their peers.\\\"\", \"from\": 288, \"to\": 431, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"This framework\", \"from\": 288, \"to\": 302}, {\"ngram\": \"toeach sport\", \"from\": 313, \"to\": 325}, {\"ngram\": \"an athlete\", \"from\": 360, \"to\": 370}, {\"ngram\": \"a disproportionate advantage\", \"from\": 381, \"to\": 409}, {\"ngram\": \"their peers\", \"from\": 418, \"to\": 429}]}, {\"sentence\": \"However, they admonish sports organizations against \\\"targeted testing \\u2026 aimed at determining [athletes'] sex, gender identity and/or sex variations.\\\"\", \"from\": 432, \"to\": 581, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"sports organizations\", \"from\": 455, \"to\": 475}, {\"ngram\": \"\\\"targeted testing\", \"from\": 484, \"to\": 501}, {\"ngram\": \"athletes'] sex\", \"from\": 526, \"to\": 540}, {\"ngram\": \"gender identity and/or sex variations\", \"from\": 542, \"to\": 579}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Instead, it's up to each sport to \\\"[provide] confidence that no athlete within a category has an unfair and disproportionate competitive advantage.\\\"\", \"from\": 582, \"to\": 730, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"each sport\", \"from\": 602, \"to\": 612}, {\"ngram\": \"confidence\", \"from\": 627, \"to\": 637}, {\"ngram\": \"no athlete\", \"from\": 643, \"to\": 653}, {\"ngram\": \"a category\", \"from\": 661, \"to\": 671}, {\"ngram\": \"an unfair and disproportionate competitive advantage\", \"from\": 676, \"to\": 728}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The IOC's sophistic gymnastics to deny sex-based categories in sport prompted 26 researchers from around the world to rebut the IOC's framework.\", \"from\": 732, \"to\": 876, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 736, \"end\": 739, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.721333966072945e-23, \"text\": \"IOC\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\"}, {\"begin\": 860, \"end\": 863, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.721333966072945e-23, \"text\": \"IOC\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"sex-based categories\", \"from\": 771, \"to\": 791}, {\"ngram\": \"sport\", \"from\": 795, \"to\": 800}, {\"ngram\": \"26 researchers\", \"from\": 810, \"to\": 824}, {\"ngram\": \"the world\", \"from\": 837, \"to\": 846}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Their paper, published last week in theScandinavian Journal of Medicine & Science in Sports, is the latest peer-reviewed study providing evidence of the obvious about sex in sports.\", \"from\": 877, \"to\": 1058, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Their paper\", \"from\": 877, \"to\": 888}, {\"ngram\": \"theScandinavian Journal\", \"from\": 913, \"to\": 936}, {\"ngram\": \"Medicine\", \"from\": 940, \"to\": 948}, {\"ngram\": \"Science\", \"from\": 951, \"to\": 958}, {\"ngram\": \"Sports\", \"from\": 962, \"to\": 968}, {\"ngram\": \"the latest peer-reviewed study providing evidence\", \"from\": 973, \"to\": 1022}, {\"ngram\": \"sex\", \"from\": 1044, \"to\": 1047}, {\"ngram\": \"sports\", \"from\": 1051, \"to\": 1057}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The researchers reviewed studies from \\\"evolutionary and developmental biology, zoology, physiology, endocrinology, medicine, sport and exercise science, [and] athletic performance results within male and female sport\\\" to refute theIOC's position that male athleteswarrant \\\"no presumption of advantage\\\" over female athletes based on \\\"biological or physiological characteristics.\\\"\", \"from\": 1060, \"to\": 1438, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The researchers\", \"from\": 1060, \"to\": 1075}, {\"ngram\": \"studies\", \"from\": 1085, \"to\": 1092}, {\"ngram\": \"evolutionary and developmental biology\", \"from\": 1099, \"to\": 1137}, {\"ngram\": \"zoology\", \"from\": 1139, \"to\": 1146}, {\"ngram\": \"physiology\", \"from\": 1148, \"to\": 1158}, {\"ngram\": \"endocrinology\", \"from\": 1160, \"to\": 1173}, {\"ngram\": \"medicine\", \"from\": 1175, \"to\": 1183}, {\"ngram\": \"sport\", \"from\": 1185, \"to\": 1190}, {\"ngram\": \"science\", \"from\": 1204, \"to\": 1211}, {\"ngram\": \"[and] athletic performance results\", \"from\": 1213, \"to\": 1247}, {\"ngram\": \"male and female sport\", \"from\": 1255, \"to\": 1276}, {\"ngram\": \"theIOC's position\", \"from\": 1288, \"to\": 1305}, {\"ngram\": \"no presumption\", \"from\": 1333, \"to\": 1347}, {\"ngram\": \"advantage\", \"from\": 1351, \"to\": 1360}, {\"ngram\": \"female athletes\", \"from\": 1367, \"to\": 1382}, {\"ngram\": \"biological or physiological characteristics\", \"from\": 1393, \"to\": 1436}]}, {\"sentence\": \"That statement \\\"is ridiculous on its face,\\\" says Kim Jones, co-founder of the Independent Council on Women's Sports (ICONS).\", \"from\": 1440, \"to\": 1564, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1489, \"end\": 1498, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kim_Jones_(designer)\", \"score\": 0.876173989494019, \"rank\": 0.09540846750147866, \"text\": \"Kim Jones\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q483501\", \"Q3501317\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kim_Jones_(designer)\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kim_Jones_(designer)\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"That statement\", \"from\": 1440, \"to\": 1454}, {\"ngram\": \"its face\", \"from\": 1473, \"to\": 1481}, {\"ngram\": \"co\", \"from\": 1500, \"to\": 1502}, {\"ngram\": \"founder\", \"from\": 1503, \"to\": 1510}, {\"ngram\": \"the Independent Council\", \"from\": 1514, \"to\": 1537}, {\"ngram\": \"Women's Sports\", \"from\": 1541, \"to\": 1555}, {\"ngram\": \"ICONS\", \"from\": 1557, \"to\": 1562}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"This is the basic knowledge we all understand and see play out in front of our eyes every day.\", \"from\": 1565, \"to\": 1660, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the basic knowledge\", \"from\": 1574, \"to\": 1593}, {\"ngram\": \"front\", \"from\": 1632, \"to\": 1637}, {\"ngram\": \"our eyes\", \"from\": 1641, \"to\": 1649}]}, {\"sentence\": \"[This new] paper is brilliant at laying out how clear the differences are between men and women.\", \"from\": 1661, \"to\": 1757, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"This new] paper\", \"from\": 1662, \"to\": 1677}, {\"ngram\": \"the differences\", \"from\": 1715, \"to\": 1730}, {\"ngram\": \"men\", \"from\": 1743, \"to\": 1746}, {\"ngram\": \"women\", \"from\": 1751, \"to\": 1756}]}, {\"sentence\": \"There are thousands of differences between male and female development in humans across the entire maturity path that result in these huge performance gaps.\\\"\", \"from\": 1758, \"to\": 1915, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"thousands\", \"from\": 1768, \"to\": 1777}, {\"ngram\": \"differences\", \"from\": 1781, \"to\": 1792}, {\"ngram\": \"male and female development\", \"from\": 1801, \"to\": 1828}, {\"ngram\": \"humans\", \"from\": 1832, \"to\": 1838}, {\"ngram\": \"the entire maturity path\", \"from\": 1846, \"to\": 1870}, {\"ngram\": \"these huge performance gaps\", \"from\": 1886, \"to\": 1913}]}, {\"sentence\": \"John Armstrong, a mathematician at King's College London who was not affiliated with this research, highlights this \\\"central flaw\\\" of the IOC's framework.\", \"from\": 1917, \"to\": 2071, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1917, \"end\": 1931, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/John_Armstrong_Sr.\", \"score\": 0.999994804945197, \"rank\": 5.195081971862065e-06, \"text\": \"John Armstrong\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/John_Armstrong_Sr.\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/John_Armstrong_Sr.\"}, {\"begin\": 1952, \"end\": 1956, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Monarch\", \"score\": 0.9958517611903911, \"rank\": 0.0040667823604652155, \"text\": \"King\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Monarch\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Monarch\"}, {\"begin\": 1967, \"end\": 1973, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\", \"score\": 0.982213739065467, \"rank\": 0.018108297700551158, \"text\": \"London\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\"}, {\"begin\": 2055, \"end\": 2058, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.721333966072945e-23, \"text\": \"IOC\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a mathematician\", \"from\": 1933, \"to\": 1948}, {\"ngram\": \"this research\", \"from\": 2002, \"to\": 2015}, {\"ngram\": \"this \\\"central flaw\", \"from\": 2028, \"to\": 2046}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"To say we should not presume male advantage in a sport unless we have specific data for that sport is like saying that just because most of the apples in a tree have fallen to the ground, one should not presume the remaining apples are also subject to gravity,\\\" he said.\", \"from\": 2072, \"to\": 2343, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"male advantage\", \"from\": 2102, \"to\": 2116}, {\"ngram\": \"a sport\", \"from\": 2120, \"to\": 2127}, {\"ngram\": \"specific data\", \"from\": 2143, \"to\": 2156}, {\"ngram\": \"that sport\", \"from\": 2161, \"to\": 2171}, {\"ngram\": \"the apples\", \"from\": 2213, \"to\": 2223}, {\"ngram\": \"a tree\", \"from\": 2227, \"to\": 2233}, {\"ngram\": \"the ground\", \"from\": 2249, \"to\": 2259}, {\"ngram\": \"one\", \"from\": 2261, \"to\": 2264}, {\"ngram\": \"the remaining apples\", \"from\": 2284, \"to\": 2304}, {\"ngram\": \"gravity\", \"from\": 2325, \"to\": 2332}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"There is overwhelming evidence of male advantage from across different sports and there is little to be gained from demonstrating this again and again, sport by sport,\\\" Armstrong noted.\", \"from\": 2345, \"to\": 2531, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2515, \"end\": 2524, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lance_Armstrong\", \"score\": 0.9999999993979145, \"rank\": 6.019342534746751e-10, \"text\": \"Armstrong\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lance_Armstrong\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lance_Armstrong\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"overwhelming evidence\", \"from\": 2355, \"to\": 2376}, {\"ngram\": \"male advantage\", \"from\": 2380, \"to\": 2394}, {\"ngram\": \"different sports\", \"from\": 2407, \"to\": 2423}, {\"ngram\": \"sport\", \"from\": 2498, \"to\": 2503}, {\"ngram\": \"sport\", \"from\": 2507, \"to\": 2512}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But even sports that have copious research into sex differences in performance have permitted males to compete in the female category at all levels of competition and age.\", \"from\": 2533, \"to\": 2704, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"even sports\", \"from\": 2537, \"to\": 2548}, {\"ngram\": \"copious research\", \"from\": 2559, \"to\": 2575}, {\"ngram\": \"sex differences\", \"from\": 2581, \"to\": 2596}, {\"ngram\": \"performance\", \"from\": 2600, \"to\": 2611}, {\"ngram\": \"males\", \"from\": 2627, \"to\": 2632}, {\"ngram\": \"the female category\", \"from\": 2647, \"to\": 2666}, {\"ngram\": \"all levels\", \"from\": 2670, \"to\": 2680}, {\"ngram\": \"competition\", \"from\": 2684, \"to\": 2695}, {\"ngram\": \"age\", \"from\": 2700, \"to\": 2703}]}, {\"sentence\": \"One path has been through misguided policies based on testosterone levels.\", \"from\": 2705, \"to\": 2779, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"One path\", \"from\": 2705, \"to\": 2713}, {\"ngram\": \"misguided policies\", \"from\": 2731, \"to\": 2749}, {\"ngram\": \"testosterone levels\", \"from\": 2759, \"to\": 2778}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Over the last decade, various sports governing bodies - including theIOCandUSA Boxing- have attempted to define females through testosterone levels.\", \"from\": 2781, \"to\": 2929, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the last decade\", \"from\": 2786, \"to\": 2801}, {\"ngram\": \"various sports\", \"from\": 2803, \"to\": 2817}, {\"ngram\": \"bodies\", \"from\": 2828, \"to\": 2834}, {\"ngram\": \"theIOCandUSA Boxing-\", \"from\": 2847, \"to\": 2867}, {\"ngram\": \"females\", \"from\": 2893, \"to\": 2900}, {\"ngram\": \"testosterone levels\", \"from\": 2909, \"to\": 2928}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Those organizationsrelied heavily on a publication by Joanna Harper, a trans-identifying male medical physicist.\", \"from\": 2930, \"to\": 3042, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2984, \"end\": 2990, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Joanna_of_Castile\", \"score\": 0.9946378949754865, \"rank\": 0.005386814601033205, \"text\": \"Joanna\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Joanna_of_Castile\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Joanna_of_Castile\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a publication\", \"from\": 2967, \"to\": 2980}, {\"ngram\": \"a trans-identifying male medical physicist\", \"from\": 2999, \"to\": 3041}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The paper consisted ofeight self-reports by trans-identifying male recreational runnerswho had suppressed their testosterone pharmacologically and recalled that they ran slower after doing so.\", \"from\": 3043, \"to\": 3235, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The paper\", \"from\": 3043, \"to\": 3052}, {\"ngram\": \"ofeight self-reports\", \"from\": 3063, \"to\": 3083}, {\"ngram\": \"trans-identifying male recreational runnerswho\", \"from\": 3087, \"to\": 3133}, {\"ngram\": \"their testosterone\", \"from\": 3149, \"to\": 3167}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Harper excluded the one respondent who said he ran faster and then concluded that males who were suppressing their testosterone could compete fairly in the female category.\", \"from\": 3236, \"to\": 3408, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Harper\", \"from\": 3236, \"to\": 3242}, {\"ngram\": \"the one respondent\", \"from\": 3252, \"to\": 3270}, {\"ngram\": \"males\", \"from\": 3318, \"to\": 3323}, {\"ngram\": \"their testosterone\", \"from\": 3345, \"to\": 3363}, {\"ngram\": \"the female category\", \"from\": 3388, \"to\": 3407}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Last week's paper builds on research by lead authors Tommy Lundberg, Emma Hilton, and others who demonstrate the persistence of male advantage after testosterone suppression.\", \"from\": 3410, \"to\": 3584, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3479, \"end\": 3483, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emma_Swan\", \"score\": 0.9951657390447808, \"rank\": 0.00253501811843281, \"text\": \"Emma\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emma_Swan\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emma_Swan\"}, {\"begin\": 3484, \"end\": 3490, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hilton_Worldwide\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.251372440364879e-20, \"text\": \"Hilton\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hilton_Worldwide\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hilton_Worldwide\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Last week's paper builds\", \"from\": 3410, \"to\": 3434}, {\"ngram\": \"research\", \"from\": 3438, \"to\": 3446}, {\"ngram\": \"lead authors Tommy Lundberg\", \"from\": 3450, \"to\": 3477}, {\"ngram\": \"others\", \"from\": 3496, \"to\": 3502}, {\"ngram\": \"the persistence\", \"from\": 3519, \"to\": 3534}, {\"ngram\": \"male advantage\", \"from\": 3538, \"to\": 3552}, {\"ngram\": \"testosterone suppression\", \"from\": 3559, \"to\": 3583}]}, {\"sentence\": \"While testosterone suppression decreases various measures of anatomy, physiology, and physical performance, those changes are a small fraction of the differences between men and women on these metrics.\", \"from\": 3586, \"to\": 3787, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"testosterone suppression\", \"from\": 3592, \"to\": 3616}, {\"ngram\": \"various measures\", \"from\": 3627, \"to\": 3643}, {\"ngram\": \"anatomy\", \"from\": 3647, \"to\": 3654}, {\"ngram\": \"physiology\", \"from\": 3656, \"to\": 3666}, {\"ngram\": \"physical performance\", \"from\": 3672, \"to\": 3692}, {\"ngram\": \"those changes\", \"from\": 3694, \"to\": 3707}, {\"ngram\": \"a small fraction\", \"from\": 3712, \"to\": 3728}, {\"ngram\": \"the differences\", \"from\": 3732, \"to\": 3747}, {\"ngram\": \"men\", \"from\": 3756, \"to\": 3759}, {\"ngram\": \"women\", \"from\": 3764, \"to\": 3769}, {\"ngram\": \"these metrics\", \"from\": 3773, \"to\": 3786}]}, {\"sentence\": \"A testosterone-suppressed male will have less muscle mass than his former self, but as a category, testosterone-suppressed men remain larger and stronger than women.\", \"from\": 3788, \"to\": 3953, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"A testosterone-suppressed male\", \"from\": 3788, \"to\": 3818}, {\"ngram\": \"less muscle mass\", \"from\": 3829, \"to\": 3845}, {\"ngram\": \"his former self\", \"from\": 3851, \"to\": 3866}, {\"ngram\": \"a category\", \"from\": 3875, \"to\": 3885}, {\"ngram\": \"testosterone-suppressed men\", \"from\": 3887, \"to\": 3914}, {\"ngram\": \"women\", \"from\": 3947, \"to\": 3952}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Further, testosterone suppression does not change attributes like height, bone length, or hip and shoulder width.\", \"from\": 3954, \"to\": 4067, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"testosterone suppression\", \"from\": 3963, \"to\": 3987}, {\"ngram\": \"attributes\", \"from\": 4004, \"to\": 4014}, {\"ngram\": \"height\", \"from\": 4020, \"to\": 4026}, {\"ngram\": \"bone length\", \"from\": 4028, \"to\": 4039}, {\"ngram\": \"hip\", \"from\": 4044, \"to\": 4047}, {\"ngram\": \"shoulder width\", \"from\": 4052, \"to\": 4066}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Even before puberty, though, males outperform females in athletic competitions.\", \"from\": 4069, \"to\": 4148, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"puberty\", \"from\": 4081, \"to\": 4088}, {\"ngram\": \"males\", \"from\": 4098, \"to\": 4103}, {\"ngram\": \"females\", \"from\": 4115, \"to\": 4122}, {\"ngram\": \"athletic competitions\", \"from\": 4126, \"to\": 4147}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Greg Brown is an exercise physiologist at the University of Nebraska at Kearney and was a co-author on the Lundberg paper.\", \"from\": 4149, \"to\": 4271, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4149, \"end\": 4159, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Greg_Brown_(folk_musician)\", \"score\": 0.9513251813464962, \"rank\": 0.01830097087379069, \"text\": \"Greg Brown\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q483501\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Greg_Brown_(folk_musician)\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Greg_Brown_(folk_musician)\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"an exercise physiologist\", \"from\": 4163, \"to\": 4187}, {\"ngram\": \"the University\", \"from\": 4191, \"to\": 4205}, {\"ngram\": \"Nebraska\", \"from\": 4209, \"to\": 4217}, {\"ngram\": \"Kearney\", \"from\": 4221, \"to\": 4228}, {\"ngram\": \"a co\", \"from\": 4237, \"to\": 4241}, {\"ngram\": \"author\", \"from\": 4242, \"to\": 4248}, {\"ngram\": \"the Lundberg paper\", \"from\": 4252, \"to\": 4270}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Brown recently published research based on national youth track and field championships.\", \"from\": 4272, \"to\": 4360, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Brown\", \"from\": 4272, \"to\": 4277}, {\"ngram\": \"research\", \"from\": 4297, \"to\": 4305}, {\"ngram\": \"national youth track and field championships\", \"from\": 4315, \"to\": 4359}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He found that by age 8, theboys ran faster in their final rounds than the girlsdid in theirs, at race distances from 100 meters to 1,500 meters.\", \"from\": 4361, \"to\": 4505, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"age\", \"from\": 4378, \"to\": 4381}, {\"ngram\": \"theboys\", \"from\": 4385, \"to\": 4392}, {\"ngram\": \"their final rounds\", \"from\": 4407, \"to\": 4425}, {\"ngram\": \"the girlsdid\", \"from\": 4431, \"to\": 4443}, {\"ngram\": \"race distances\", \"from\": 4458, \"to\": 4472}, {\"ngram\": \"100 meters\", \"from\": 4478, \"to\": 4488}, {\"ngram\": \"1,500 meters\", \"from\": 4492, \"to\": 4504}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Brown's article came out a few months after John Armstrong (mentioned above), sociologist Alice Sullivan of University College London, and I published a paper on the role ofsex versus gender expression in distance running.\", \"from\": 4507, \"to\": 4729, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4551, \"end\": 4565, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/John_Armstrong_Sr.\", \"score\": 0.999994804945197, \"rank\": 5.195081971862065e-06, \"text\": \"John Armstrong\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/John_Armstrong_Sr.\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/John_Armstrong_Sr.\"}, {\"begin\": 4615, \"end\": 4640, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/University_College_London\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.7905837545944265e-33, \"text\": \"University College London\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q3918\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q2385804\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/University_College_London\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/University_College_London\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Brown's article\", \"from\": 4507, \"to\": 4522}, {\"ngram\": \"a paper\", \"from\": 4658, \"to\": 4665}, {\"ngram\": \"the role ofsex\", \"from\": 4669, \"to\": 4683}, {\"ngram\": \"gender expression\", \"from\": 4691, \"to\": 4708}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Having been on the receiving end of many tweets and articles saying, \\\"Duh, obvious, did we need research to prove this?\\\"\", \"from\": 4730, \"to\": 4850, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the receiving end\", \"from\": 4745, \"to\": 4762}, {\"ngram\": \"many tweets\", \"from\": 4766, \"to\": 4777}, {\"ngram\": \"articles\", \"from\": 4782, \"to\": 4790}, {\"ngram\": \"research\", \"from\": 4826, \"to\": 4834}]}, {\"sentence\": \"I asked Brown if we really needed quantitative research to prove that boys run faster than girls.\", \"from\": 4851, \"to\": 4948, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Brown\", \"from\": 4859, \"to\": 4864}, {\"ngram\": \"quantitative research\", \"from\": 4885, \"to\": 4906}, {\"ngram\": \"boys\", \"from\": 4921, \"to\": 4925}, {\"ngram\": \"girls\", \"from\": 4942, \"to\": 4947}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Some court cases regarding transgender athletes competing in girls' sports said there is no evidence of prepubescent sex-based differences.\", \"from\": 4950, \"to\": 5090, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Some court cases\", \"from\": 4951, \"to\": 4967}, {\"ngram\": \"transgender athletes\", \"from\": 4978, \"to\": 4998}, {\"ngram\": \"girls' sports\", \"from\": 5012, \"to\": 5025}, {\"ngram\": \"no evidence\", \"from\": 5040, \"to\": 5051}, {\"ngram\": \"prepubescent sex-based differences\", \"from\": 5055, \"to\": 5089}]}, {\"sentence\": \"This kind of work does matter to inform policy.\", \"from\": 5091, \"to\": 5138, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"This kind\", \"from\": 5091, \"to\": 5100}, {\"ngram\": \"work\", \"from\": 5104, \"to\": 5108}, {\"ngram\": \"policy\", \"from\": 5131, \"to\": 5137}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Moreover, it can be useful to evaluate the obvious because some of the things we take for granted as truth, maybe they are not,\\\" Brown said.\", \"from\": 5139, \"to\": 5279, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the things\", \"from\": 5206, \"to\": 5216}, {\"ngram\": \"truth\", \"from\": 5240, \"to\": 5245}, {\"ngram\": \"Brown\", \"from\": 5268, \"to\": 5273}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The obvious question in response to this accumulation of \\\"obvious\\\" data is: What will it take to restore and enforce sex-based categories in sports at all levels?\", \"from\": 5281, \"to\": 5443, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The obvious question\", \"from\": 5281, \"to\": 5301}, {\"ngram\": \"response\", \"from\": 5305, \"to\": 5313}, {\"ngram\": \"this accumulation\", \"from\": 5317, \"to\": 5334}, {\"ngram\": \"\\\"obvious\\\" data\", \"from\": 5338, \"to\": 5352}, {\"ngram\": \"sex-based categories\", \"from\": 5398, \"to\": 5418}, {\"ngram\": \"sports\", \"from\": 5422, \"to\": 5428}, {\"ngram\": \"all levels\", \"from\": 5432, \"to\": 5442}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Even if the International Olympic Committee aligned its policies with the Lundberg paper, the IOC is not binding on youth sports, grassroots sports, or even the NCAA.\", \"from\": 5444, \"to\": 5610, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5456, \"end\": 5487, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"International Olympic Committee\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\"}, {\"begin\": 5538, \"end\": 5541, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.721333966072945e-23, \"text\": \"IOC\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\"}, {\"begin\": 5605, \"end\": 5609, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Collegiate_Athletic_Association\", \"score\": 0.9988810668990985, \"rank\": 0.0011076722531590027, \"text\": \"NCAA\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Collegiate_Athletic_Association\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Collegiate_Athletic_Association\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"its policies\", \"from\": 5496, \"to\": 5508}, {\"ngram\": \"the Lundberg paper\", \"from\": 5514, \"to\": 5532}, {\"ngram\": \"youth sports\", \"from\": 5560, \"to\": 5572}, {\"ngram\": \"grassroots sports\", \"from\": 5574, \"to\": 5591}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Brown is optimistic about \\\"the grassroots level, where girls and women's sports will start being limited to female athletes.\", \"from\": 5612, \"to\": 5736, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Brown\", \"from\": 5612, \"to\": 5617}, {\"ngram\": \"\\\"the grassroots level\", \"from\": 5638, \"to\": 5659}, {\"ngram\": \"girls\", \"from\": 5667, \"to\": 5672}, {\"ngram\": \"women\", \"from\": 5677, \"to\": 5682}, {\"ngram\": \"sports\", \"from\": 5685, \"to\": 5691}, {\"ngram\": \"female athletes\", \"from\": 5720, \"to\": 5735}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Some school districts and other local organizations are making female-only sports policies when state or higher-level organizations will not.\\\"\", \"from\": 5737, \"to\": 5879, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Some school districts\", \"from\": 5737, \"to\": 5758}, {\"ngram\": \"other local organizations\", \"from\": 5763, \"to\": 5788}, {\"ngram\": \"female-only sports policies\", \"from\": 5800, \"to\": 5827}, {\"ngram\": \"state or higher-level organizations\", \"from\": 5833, \"to\": 5868}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Brown noted thelawsuit against the NCAAby female athletes will \\\"make those in charge of sports have second thoughts about their transgender inclusion policies.\", \"from\": 5881, \"to\": 6040, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Brown\", \"from\": 5881, \"to\": 5886}, {\"ngram\": \"thelawsuit\", \"from\": 5893, \"to\": 5903}, {\"ngram\": \"the NCAAby female athletes\", \"from\": 5912, \"to\": 5938}, {\"ngram\": \"charge\", \"from\": 5959, \"to\": 5965}, {\"ngram\": \"sports\", \"from\": 5969, \"to\": 5975}, {\"ngram\": \"second thoughts\", \"from\": 5981, \"to\": 5996}, {\"ngram\": \"their transgender inclusion policies\", \"from\": 6003, \"to\": 6039}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Before there was a fear oflawsuits from transgender activists, but now the shoe is on the other foot.\\\"\", \"from\": 6041, \"to\": 6143, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a fear oflawsuits\", \"from\": 6058, \"to\": 6075}, {\"ngram\": \"transgender activists\", \"from\": 6081, \"to\": 6102}, {\"ngram\": \"the shoe\", \"from\": 6112, \"to\": 6120}, {\"ngram\": \"the other foot\", \"from\": 6127, \"to\": 6141}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He also called on \\\"scholarly journals, sports science organizations, and sports scientists to speak out and keep the reality of sex-based differences in sports performance in the news to counteract the 20-year head start the transgender activists have.\\\"\", \"from\": 6145, \"to\": 6398, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"scholarly journals\", \"from\": 6164, \"to\": 6182}, {\"ngram\": \"sports science organizations\", \"from\": 6184, \"to\": 6212}, {\"ngram\": \"sports scientists\", \"from\": 6218, \"to\": 6235}, {\"ngram\": \"the reality\", \"from\": 6258, \"to\": 6269}, {\"ngram\": \"sex-based differences\", \"from\": 6273, \"to\": 6294}, {\"ngram\": \"sports performance\", \"from\": 6298, \"to\": 6316}, {\"ngram\": \"the news\", \"from\": 6320, \"to\": 6328}, {\"ngram\": \"the 20-year head\", \"from\": 6343, \"to\": 6359}, {\"ngram\": \"the transgender activists\", \"from\": 6366, \"to\": 6391}]}, {\"sentence\": \"ICONS is funding the lawsuit that Brown mentioned.\", \"from\": 6400, \"to\": 6450, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"ICONS\", \"from\": 6400, \"to\": 6405}, {\"ngram\": \"the lawsuit\", \"from\": 6417, \"to\": 6428}, {\"ngram\": \"Brown\", \"from\": 6434, \"to\": 6439}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"We need people to realize there can be no fear and no shame in standing up for women.\", \"from\": 6451, \"to\": 6537, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"people\", \"from\": 6460, \"to\": 6466}, {\"ngram\": \"no fear\", \"from\": 6491, \"to\": 6498}, {\"ngram\": \"no shame\", \"from\": 6503, \"to\": 6511}, {\"ngram\": \"women\", \"from\": 6531, \"to\": 6536}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It's a basic message that we all have the responsibility to communicate clearly,\\\" said ICONS co-founder Kim Jones.\", \"from\": 6538, \"to\": 6652, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6642, \"end\": 6651, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kim_Jones_(designer)\", \"score\": 0.876173989494019, \"rank\": 0.09540846750147866, \"text\": \"Kim Jones\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q483501\", \"Q3501317\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kim_Jones_(designer)\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kim_Jones_(designer)\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a basic message\", \"from\": 6543, \"to\": 6558}, {\"ngram\": \"the responsibility\", \"from\": 6576, \"to\": 6594}, {\"ngram\": \"ICONS\", \"from\": 6625, \"to\": 6630}, {\"ngram\": \"co\", \"from\": 6631, \"to\": 6633}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"The stories of women and girls being robbed of fair sport, or even facing injury, are the path of change.\", \"from\": 6653, \"to\": 6759, \"entities\"